				<td colspan="2"><span>WHY is everyone whining so much?  Yeah they DID make some of our best tricks harder post 65 (and took away AOE kiting).... 
<br />

<br />
But Kinkzor.. this is NOT an idiotic change.  I would be happier if it was a 40 range, but this is a GODSEND.
<br />

<br />
At 70, swarm kiting will be nigh on impossible, or at least REAL tough.. OK... But what do we GET?  
<br />
The ability to effectively use charm for crowd control... something LACKING since sometime in the 50's
<br />
1-on-1 charm kiting with level 68 mobs instead of level 57
<br />

<br />
Quite frankly.. as someone who has swarmed a fair bit...If I could do to level 65 mobs what I do with level 57 mobs now... it would be unbalancing.  No class could come close... and grouping... would be something I did for the benefit of my friends, since the xps would so relatively suck.
<br />

<br />
Frankly with this new charm I'd like to go solo Vxed.  No need for that silly group that the enchanters need to pull it off, just run/mez/mez/recharm.  Solo would be workable... duo with a shaman would be real nice... pet hasted... yummy
<br />

<br />
The funny thing is... Back when they gave us the mana-eating, 1 minute charm.... many bards SCREAMED nerf.  In FACT it WAS a nerf to swarm kiting, or intended to be.  Suck down the mana.. limit the time... make it a minute so its &quot;harder&quot; to swarm them, force 1-on-1 charming.  Of course now... there are several bards that think you cant swarm until level 39... ROFL.  The nerf made us stronger.
<br />

<br />
Then with the POP expansion, the level 57 limit ... scream nerf again.  Frankly that IS in my way.  I WANT to charm in groups, it is a fantastic value add.. and I CAN'T because we aren't killing pissy little level 57 mobs.  But with it I CAN get decent xps while lfg or when I don't have time to group.
<br />

<br />
But to call a new song a nerf.. a new song that GIVES US what many bards have been clamouring for.. thats just silly.  You are a bard... adapt... find the hole in the nerf that makes it overpowering.  Use it and be the best class in the game.  Thats what we DO.
<br />

<br />

