<br />

<br />
Good point about the aggro difference.
<br />

<br />
If you have a pet on your side being sacrificed to 20 mobs...that is a swarm
<br />

<br />
If you have 20 mobs and <b>no pet</b>...that is an area kite if the song lands on all them, or a chant kite if it hits one in the massive kite.
<br />

<br />
If you have a pet that tanks for you while you chant and help the pet out...this is charm like we better get used to with the lv70 tune.
<br />

<br />
The range is not going to stop the swarm kiting with your lv 68 pet getting smoked.  It will be the summoning, casters, snares, huge dammage no room for any error, stuns that will make swarm kitting very difficult.  Go and try a swarm kite in HOH with this new tune...be a piece of cake and the mob limit of 10 will take care of the massive kite for ya.  Pet will die quick, but not too quick.
