				<td colspan="2"><span>No problems whatsoever pulling in WoS. To start, you don't need to single. Mezz one on the pull and let it come when mezz breaks, re-mezz in camp. Very low mezz resist rate.  Most mobs don't see invis, so vis up and look around. There's usually a good angle to aggro pull that limits the number of mobs to two. So you're set.
<br />

<br />
I pulled MPG all night and only faded twice. Mobs are spaced out there, just a few roamers to keep an eye our for. Anybody can pull there. 
<br />

<br />
200 mana for a charm seems reasonable to me. If you nave FT15 and MC4, you'll get that back long before the next mob you'll need charm comes along. I'm not talking about keeping the pet, just using the extra dps and then killing it after. Charm breaks, mezz. Or possibly using to off tank if you have three. As long as the other one gets slowed and rooted, I could refresh charm. And you don't have the FT, work for it. But don't complain that the mana cost is too high becuase you don't yet have the gear. You will.
<br />

<br />
One of my all time best experiences in EQ was when I was 53 (an alt at the time and not twinked) and was invited by a friend to help him with the shaman epic in the Hole. He was 58 and his six friends were all 65 and very urber. This was about a year and a half ago, so well before lodn. At first I was mezzing and stuff and they told me it was a waste of time. So I started charming and they just laughed at me. Everything went well to the castle. They wasted the epic mob, my buddy got his piece. But no porter and they were getting bored. So instead of fighting back out of the castle, we IVU'd. 
<br />

<br />
Which was fine until someone forgot that we were crossing the border between the undead and the normal mobs and got aggro. We ran up the ramp with about eight mobs. I charmed one, it fought one mob. I mezzed two others. I felt good because I single handly took care of four mobs while they went about killing the other four. Of course, if you know the area, there are a lot of roaming mobs. So they kept coming. And coming. When the last of the urber group died, he lay upon a truely impressive number of bodies. And they left two mobs extra mobs for me. Luckily, someone had healed me before the last gasp, so I was full health. And shortly after I mezzed the first of the new adds, my pet died. So I charmed the second one and it made quick work of my former pet. I'm back down to one charmed mob fighting and two mezzed. When it got down to one mezzed, I tried to camp while pulsing mezz, but this act cause the mob to forget my pet and come after me, so no salvation there. Respawn started in the vicitiny and my minutes were numbered. I lived long enough to have the level one halfling rogue dragging bodies tell me to die already so he could drag. A small triumph I suppose, but I'll never forget it.
<br />

<br />
Charm was fun. I'm so looking forward to it.</span></td>
